  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Slice the onion and set aside. Peel and quarter your potatoes. Boil for around 25 minutes."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get on with making your paste. Slice up your shallots, spring onions and lemongrass. Add this to a blender along with your garlic, chilli powder, galangal, ginger, coriander seeds, cumin, star anise, cinnamon, cloves, cardamom, kaffir lime leaf, pepper and turmeric. Add a good glug of olive oil. Blend until it forms a smooth paste."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get your rice on (see pack instructions)."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Pour a drizzle of olive oil into a hot wok or cassorole dish. Add in the onions and fry for 5 mins, until softened. Stir in your Massaman paste, once you can smell the aromas from the paste, pour in your coconut milk. Refill the can with water and pour into the pan."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Bring the pan to the boil and add your chicken, your cooked potatoes, sugar, onion powder and soy sauce. Allow the curry to reduce on a medium-low heat until you have a nice thick sauce."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "When the curry has reduced, add your peanuts. It’s now ready to serve on a bed of rice. Top with a sprinkle of peanuts and tuck into this delicious Thai classic."
    }
  ],
